<h1>@HI{{sore deha}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> <strong>@HI{{sore deha}}</strong> ...
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<strong>@HI{{sore deha}}</strong> is a conjunction which means "if that is the case ...".
<p></p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      A: @HI{{kono @KT{{orenji}}ha @KJ{{sweet}}kunai desu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      B: @HI{{<strong>sore deha</strong> kore ha dou desuka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      A: This orange is not sweet.
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      B: How about this one then?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

<h2> Notes </h2>

@HI{{<strong>sore deha</strong>}} becomes @HI{{sore ja}} in informal speech.
<p></p>

@HI{{<strong>sore deha</strong>}} sometimes shortens to @HI{{deha}} which then become @HI{{ja}} in informal speech.
<p></p>

@HI{{<strong>sore deha</strong>}} is found at the beginning of a sentence and the @HI{{sore}} refers to something already mentioned.
<p></p>

